Undocumented workers there can expect to receive up to $1,000 per household, and can begin applying next month.
Through the Arizona Health Care Cost Containment System, they can apply for free emergency care.
In Arizona, undocumented immigrants paid about $213.6 million in state and local taxes in 2014, the most recent year for which figures are available.